    "what_description": "Selliguea hastata is a species of fern in the family Polypodiaceae. It has a rhizome with scales and creeping stoloniferous fronds, 0.3-0.8 meters long, and divided into pinnae, which are further divided into pinnules. The rhachis and rachides are brown and hairy. The frond is ovate-lanceolate and has a rounded base, with a long, narrow tip. The plant has sporangia in sori on the underside of the frond, with 64 spores per sporangium.",
