    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Selliguea hastata are rooted in its antimicrobial activity, which prevents the growth of various pathogens and is attributed to its flavonoid and phenolic compounds. Additionally, the antioxidant property of Selliguea hastata protects the body from oxidative stress and cell damage, which is a result of the plant's high content of saponins and volatile oils. The anti-inflammatory property of Selliguea hastata reduces inflammation and pain by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes, which is due to the presence of sesquiterpenes and flavonoids. Furthermore, Selliguea hastata exhibits analgesic activity by blocking pain receptors and has been found to contain alkaloids and saponins responsible for this effect. The antipyretic property of Selliguea hastata is also notable, which is a result of its ability to reduce fever and is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and glycosides.",
