    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Selliguea hastata improperly include experiencing nausea due to its emetic properties, which can cause vomiting and stomach discomfort. Developing diarrhea is another potential side effect, as the plant contains compounds that can irritate the digestive system and increase bowel movements. Experiencing nausea and develop diarrhea are often reported side effects, especially when the plant is ingested in large quantities or without proper preparation. Selliguea hastata contains saponins, which can cause gastrointestinal upset and other adverse effects when used improperly. The improper use of Selliguea hastata can also lead to other side effects, such as stomach pain and dizziness, although these are not as well-documented as nausea and diarrhea.",
    "uses": "Selliguea hastata, a plant native to various parts of the world, has been traditionally used in folk medicine to treat various health conditions. The leaves of this plant are said to possess anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which contribute to its medicinal uses. In some cultures, the plant is used to treat fever, cough, and other respiratory issues. Additionally, Selliguea hastata is believed to have antiseptic properties, making it useful for wound healing and skin care. Further research is needed to fully understand the plant's medicinal potential and its effects on human health.",
    "taxonomy": "Selliguea hastata is classified in the family Polypodiaceae, which is a group of ferns. It belongs to the genus Selliguea, a genus of ferns commonly found in tropical and subtropical regions. The species Selliguea hastata is native to Asia and is known for its unique leaf structure. The classification of Selliguea hastata is further broken down into its kingdom (Plantae), phylum (Polypodiophyta), and class (Polypodiopsida). This classification helps in understanding the evolutionary relationships and characteristics of the species.",
    "benefits": "Selliguea hastata is traditionally used in herbal medicine, with reported health benefits including anti-inflammatory properties and the ability to lower blood sugar levels. Its leaves are used to treat various ailments such as fever, skin conditions, and respiratory issues. The plant is also believed to have antimicrobial properties, helping to combat infections. Moreover, Selliguea hastata is sometimes used as a natural remedy for digestive problems and headaches. However, its effectiveness and safety for human consumption should be confirmed by further scientific research.",
    "parts": "Selliguea hastata is known to be a medicinal plant, and its leaves are used in traditional medicine. The leaves contain various compounds with potential health benefits, including antioxidants and anti-inflammatory properties. The plant's leaves are typically harvested and dried for later use in medicinal preparations. In traditional medicine, the leaves are often used to treat various ailments, including fever, rheumatism, and skin conditions. The leaves' medicinal properties are attributed to their rich content of tannins and other bioactive compounds.",
    "intro": "Selliguea hastata, also known as Polypodium hastatum or Selaginella hastata, is a type of pteridophyte, a plant that belongs to the division Pteridophyta, characterized by the production of spores for reproduction. The plant is traditionally used in herbal medicine to treat various health conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and respiratory issues, thanks to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. The bioactive constituents of Selliguea hastata include flavonoids, alkaloids, and terpenoids, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. In traditional herbal medicine, Selliguea hastata is commonly prepared as a decoction or infusion, as well as being used in the form of tinctures and essential oils."
